cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection and semantic segmentation, which are common tasks in computer vision. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a framework that incorporates multiple types of supervisions and light-weight modules. Additionally, it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it aims to improve the performance of autonomous systems such as self-driving cars and unmanned surface vessels. The robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is also a possibility as the proposed framework could be applied to robotics tasks. Finally, the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of object detection and segmentation in security-related applications.
